            "message": "Make extension compatible with Firefox\n\nThis commit makes the extension compatible with Firefox by doing the following:\n\n* Split out `window.location` into the component parts used by the extension (`href`, `host`, `origin` and `pathname`) since Firefox does not allow `window.location` to be used directly in extensions\n* Add `undefined;` at the end of all content scripts, since they need to return something\n* Add a charset to the popup HTML to remove a warning\n* Swap the order of executed scripts in `popup.js` since the content script depends on `window.highlightComponent` being defined\n* Add a `font-face` CSS declaration since Firefox uses Times New Roman as its default font (now the current system font will be used)\n* Give `tabs` permission to the extension to allow it to access current tab details\n* Fix a few lint-type issues",

            "message": "Add links based on content item\n\nThis adds a bunch of useful links to the popup.\n\n- An Edit-link that leads to the publishing application. For some\napplications we can infer a deeplink from the content_id (like\ncollections-publisher). For others we either link to a prefilled search\npath (publisher) or link to the publishing app main page.\n- Link to content-tagger (where anything can be tagged) and\nsearch-admin (where you can see what raw information rummager holds)\n- Links to the rendering app was already available in the popup, but we\nnow use the content item for this. This means that the link is also\navailable on pages that 404, 410 and 5XX. Previously this link was\nbased on a meta-tag which wouldn't be present on clobbered error pages.\n- A similar link to the GitHub of the publishing application. In some\ncases this needs some mapping, because the `publishing_app` in content\nstore isn't always the repo name. Make a PR if you find more exceptions.\n- Link to the content schema on GitHub.\n- A link to the brand new publishing-api debug page, which is initially\nonly available in development\n(https://github.com/alphagov/publishing-api/pull/345).\n\nThe way we generate these links is by fetching the content-item from\nthe content-store when the user opens the popup. This means a slight\ndelay between opening and the extension populating the menu.",
